# Backlog

<!-- This file tracks all work items for the project. -->

## Folder structure

| Folder | Contains |
|---|---|
| `proposed/` | Items that are proposed, ready, or in progress. |
| `done/` | Completed items (kept for traceability). |
| `archived-cr/` | Items closed without implementation (changed requirements, superseded, etc.). |

## Agents

| Agent | Owns |
|---|---|
| Backlog-Planner | Creates and updates items in `proposed/`. |
| Change-Orchestrator | Implements items, moves them to `done/` or `archived-cr/`. |

## Conventions

- IDs follow the pattern `BG-NNN` (zero-padded to three digits).
- Next available ID: `BG-001`.
- Priority tiers: **P0** (blocking), **P1** (next), **P2** (soon), **P3** (later).

### Status lifecycle

`Proposed` -> `Ready` -> `In Progress` -> `Done`

Only the Change-Orchestrator sets `Ready`, `In Progress`, or `Done`.

